1
00:00:40,541 --> 00:00:43,141
CJ ENM presents

2
00:00:43,541 --> 00:00:46,061
a THE LAMP.ltd production

3
00:00:56,181 --> 00:00:58,061
To Phantom

4
00:00:58,101 --> 00:01:00,101
Commence the operation

5
00:01:00,141 --> 00:01:02,221
Do not stop

6
00:01:02,261 --> 00:01:03,741
- until it succeeds
- This just in!

7
00:01:03,741 --> 00:01:06,981
Last night, in Shanghai,
an assassination attempt was made

8
00:01:07,021 --> 00:01:09,261
upon the next Governor-General to Joseon.

9
00:01:10,261 --> 00:01:13,261
A group of terrorists known as the
'Shadow Corps'

10
00:01:13,301 --> 00:01:15,981
has been coordinating organized crime

11
00:01:16,021 --> 00:01:18,581
using a network of spies
known as 'Phantom.'

12
00:01:18,941 --> 00:01:21,821
A violent shootout ensued.

13
00:01:22,021 --> 00:01:25,461
All terrorists were killed.

14
00:01:25,701 --> 00:01:28,661
There were no survivors.

15
00:01:52,781 --> 00:01:55,021
A new day has dawned.

16
00:01:55,061 --> 00:01:56,781
May your day be full of promise.

17
00:02:00,781 --> 00:02:03,141
Intelligence Department,
Japanese Government-General

18
00:02:32,821 --> 00:02:34,301
From no. 5.

19
00:02:39,301 --> 00:02:42,141
Intelligence report

20
00:02:46,061 --> 00:02:48,021
Supervisor
Murayama Junji

21
00:03:18,941 --> 00:03:23,221
79. It's sunny today

22
00:03:24,221 --> 00:03:26,541
It's sunny today.

23
00:03:31,621 --> 00:03:36,381
New Governor-General
to visit Joseon Shrine

24
00:03:36,421 --> 00:03:40,261
Cryptography officer
Cheon Eunho

25
00:04:03,861 --> 00:04:06,301
Are you spying on me?

26
00:04:07,181 --> 00:04:09,701
I'm here in an official capacity.

27
00:04:11,461 --> 00:04:12,901
Get a move on, then.

28
00:04:52,621 --> 00:04:56,221
Cafe Gold

29
00:05:07,421 --> 00:05:08,701
One ticket, please.

30
00:06:35,301 --> 00:06:37,621
New Governor-General
in Kyungsung

31
00:06:37,661 --> 00:06:41,101
Eliminate him at Joseon Shrine

32
00:07:05,861 --> 00:07:08,261
Can I borrow a light?

33
00:07:48,141 --> 00:07:49,861
You need your matches.

34
00:08:21,181 --> 00:08:24,341
I heard about the mishap in Shanghai.

35
00:08:24,981 --> 00:08:27,981
You can relax here in Kyungsung, sir.

36
00:08:29,381 --> 00:08:34,581
We have a strong hold over this region.

37
00:08:36,861 --> 00:08:41,021
You can focus on the inauguration.

38
00:08:46,061 --> 00:08:48,421
It's been a while back in Kyungsung?

39
00:08:49,301 --> 00:08:51,221
It must feel

40
00:08:53,301 --> 00:08:54,541
foreign.

41
00:09:14,941 --> 00:09:17,021
First column from the left!

42
00:09:17,981 --> 00:09:18,941
Attention!

43
00:09:21,341 --> 00:09:22,821
All attention!

44
00:09:23,781 --> 00:09:24,781
Formation!

45
00:09:30,221 --> 00:09:34,941
The Guards Division act like
they run the place already.

46
00:09:43,061 --> 00:09:44,141
Formation

47
00:09:57,781 --> 00:10:01,861
It's our great honor to have you
as the new Governor-General of Joseon!

48
00:10:02,381 --> 00:10:05,461
My service is entirely at your disposal.

49
00:10:05,501 --> 00:10:06,821
Enough out of you!

50
00:10:08,381 --> 00:10:09,981
Governor-General,

51
00:10:10,021 --> 00:10:13,901
did you have a chance
to try Naengmyeon?

52
00:10:14,421 --> 00:10:15,501
Naengmyeon?

53
00:10:16,221 --> 00:10:19,221
They say the term "Naengmyeon"
comes from China.

54
00:10:19,301 --> 00:10:21,381
But I'm not sure.

55
00:10:21,781 --> 00:10:26,621
I always wanted to let you try Naengmyeon.

56
00:10:26,981 --> 00:10:32,741
At first, Naengmyeon were accompanied
by first-class beef, but later...

57
00:10:46,661 --> 00:10:48,381
Platoon 2, follow me!

58
00:11:06,901 --> 00:11:07,741
This way, sir.

59
00:11:07,781 --> 00:11:11,901
You useless idiots!

60
00:11:15,421 --> 00:11:18,541
Guards! Come and help him.

61
00:11:20,861 --> 00:11:24,501
Let me help you.

62
00:12:07,981 --> 00:12:09,301
Nanyoung...

63
00:14:09,101 --> 00:14:10,061
Murayama.

64
00:14:10,661 --> 00:14:11,661
Takahara.

65
00:14:13,061 --> 00:14:14,781
Multiple shots fired,

66
00:14:17,981 --> 00:14:19,101
but no catch.

67
00:14:58,901 --> 00:15:00,461
Should I question them one by one?

68
00:15:03,421 --> 00:15:04,821
Not yet.

69
00:15:16,781 --> 00:15:18,541
Phantoms...

70
00:15:18,781 --> 00:15:24,621
You said you wiped them out
in Shanghai?

71
00:15:25,181 --> 00:15:28,621
Kyungsung was a blind spot for us.

72
00:15:29,861 --> 00:15:32,621
I'm at fault, sir.

73
00:15:46,061 --> 00:15:47,461
Fault...

74
00:15:54,381 --> 00:15:56,941
On my first day in Joseon?

75
00:16:02,461 --> 00:16:07,781
I'll make sure we're in the clear.

76
00:16:09,381 --> 00:16:17,061
I just declared
a non-military rule policy.

77
00:16:19,701 --> 00:16:22,301
See that it's done quietly.

78
00:16:48,261 --> 00:16:49,541
Wipe the place out!

79
00:17:22,541 --> 00:17:23,541
The Phantom

80
00:17:24,901 --> 00:17:26,421
I'm sure you've heard of it.

81
00:17:30,021 --> 00:17:34,261
Yesterday's attack resembles
the Shanghai terror.

82
00:17:35,781 --> 00:17:37,341
The Guards Division suspects

83
00:17:37,781 --> 00:17:40,581
that a Phantom has infiltrated
the Government-General office.

84
00:17:41,101 --> 00:17:43,381
How come you're telling me this?

85
00:17:43,421 --> 00:17:44,741
To give you the upper hand.

86
00:17:52,061 --> 00:17:55,981
The Police Department has always
had command over Joseon.

87
00:17:56,861 --> 00:18:00,261
You can't let the Guards Division
take control away from you.

88
00:18:01,981 --> 00:18:04,581
Whoever catches the Phantom
will get the upper hand.

89
00:18:05,861 --> 00:18:09,061
Reinstate me to the Police Department.

90
00:18:14,661 --> 00:18:17,821
You don't give up, do you?

91
00:18:20,181 --> 00:18:23,901
But to what end?

92
00:18:33,781 --> 00:18:34,821
One, please.

93
00:18:57,341 --> 00:19:00,381
Cafe Gold

94
00:21:14,941 --> 00:21:15,781
It's me.

95
00:21:16,501 --> 00:21:18,701
I saw the Chief Guard in the theater.

96
00:21:19,301 --> 00:21:22,981
He led anti-Phantom operations
in Shanghai.

97
00:21:23,901 --> 00:21:24,861
Be careful.

98
00:21:25,621 --> 00:21:30,221
I'm prepared.
My time will come when it comes.

99
00:21:30,701 --> 00:21:32,781
Well, don't think about dying first.

100
00:21:34,341 --> 00:21:37,621
Nanyoung must've been the same.

101
00:21:39,221 --> 00:21:42,621
Enough blood has been shed.
Let's stop it now.

102
00:22:10,341 --> 00:22:13,581
I'm sorry, but today's showing is over.

103
00:22:18,341 --> 00:22:19,421
How curious...

104
00:22:21,141 --> 00:22:25,941
there is a movie theater
in this neighborhood

105
00:22:29,621 --> 00:22:32,021
that's run by a Korean?

106
00:23:00,381 --> 00:23:03,461
We took the liberty of packing,
due to time constraints.

107
00:23:17,061 --> 00:23:19,581
Shouldn't you at least tell me
where we're going?

108
00:24:32,381 --> 00:24:37,781
I had the weirdest dream last night
about snakes.

109
00:24:38,981 --> 00:24:43,141
50 or so silvery snakes were
squirming in a big silver basin.

110
00:24:45,101 --> 00:24:47,701
What do you think it means?

111
00:24:57,461 --> 00:25:00,141
What a trouble being dragged here
out of the blue!

112
00:25:03,981 --> 00:25:04,821
Here.

113
00:25:06,741 --> 00:25:08,701
Did you get car sick?

114
00:25:09,301 --> 00:25:14,981
Well, I threw up 3 times.
Take a seat.

115
00:25:17,461 --> 00:25:20,101
Have you heard anything?
At all?

116
00:25:21,701 --> 00:25:23,901
Why bother? She's got 'clueless'
written all over her face.

117
00:25:25,341 --> 00:25:26,901
It's written all over all our faces.

118
00:25:28,101 --> 00:25:30,421
Look, she's from
the Deputy Governor's office.

119
00:25:31,101 --> 00:25:33,901
He's from the Police department,
and we're from Intelligence...

120
00:25:34,421 --> 00:25:36,021
Nothing in common.

121
00:25:36,061 --> 00:25:37,861
So then why are we all here?

122
00:25:39,861 --> 00:25:41,941
If anyone would know, it's you.

123
00:25:42,541 --> 00:25:45,021
You have a different background than us.

124
00:25:52,821 --> 00:25:55,781
Where are you from?

125
00:25:56,981 --> 00:25:58,381
Who put you up to this?

126
00:26:00,221 --> 00:26:02,901
These fuckers are playing dumb with me.

127
00:26:02,981 --> 00:26:05,581
I'm the Deputy Governor-General's
head secretary!

128
00:26:05,581 --> 00:26:08,181
Quiet down.

129
00:26:09,981 --> 00:26:12,621
You may be the head secretary,
but you're not the Deputy himself.

130
00:26:14,821 --> 00:26:16,381
You quiet down.

131
00:26:18,101 --> 00:26:21,181
With the Police department?
You were demoted a long time ago.

132
00:26:22,341 --> 00:26:24,021
Shame on you.

133
00:26:24,781 --> 00:26:28,381
What are you doing here?
You went back to your hometown.

134
00:26:28,421 --> 00:26:29,581
Your mother's ill.

135
00:26:32,821 --> 00:26:36,061
I was on my way when I got taken in.

136
00:26:55,581 --> 00:26:59,821
It took some time to gather all of you.

137
00:27:00,821 --> 00:27:03,221
Let me introduce myself properly.

138
00:27:09,061 --> 00:27:14,381
I'm Chief Guard to the
new Governor-General Yamagata,

139
00:27:15,261 --> 00:27:17,701
Takahara Kaito.

140
00:27:20,621 --> 00:27:22,461
The Gold Theater in Gold Avenue,

141
00:27:23,741 --> 00:27:27,141
I brought something back from there.

142
00:27:34,341 --> 00:27:35,621
Dracula?

143
00:27:36,461 --> 00:27:40,381
A blood-thirsty demon
that wakes up at night?

144
00:27:42,901 --> 00:27:46,141
I found something interesting
on the bottom of the poster.

145
00:27:47,221 --> 00:27:52,941
It might seem like a print error,
but no, it's more than that.

146
00:27:53,581 --> 00:27:56,181
It's a code.

147
00:27:57,821 --> 00:28:00,861
Mr. Cheon, you're an expert
in cryptography.

148
00:28:02,221 --> 00:28:03,741
Would you do the honors?

149
00:28:10,541 --> 00:28:14,061
But this is a complex cypher
composed of two different...

150
00:28:15,061 --> 00:28:19,381
This is a complex cypher
composed of two different systems.

151
00:28:19,421 --> 00:28:22,541
I'll need a decoding book.

152
00:28:33,541 --> 00:28:37,461
The Shadow Corps
based in Shanghai

153
00:28:38,541 --> 00:28:41,301
infiltrated the Chinese Intelligence

154
00:28:42,581 --> 00:28:47,061
with secret agents known as
"Phantoms."

155
00:28:48,461 --> 00:28:51,941
I thought Kyungsung was safe.

156
00:28:52,981 --> 00:28:55,421
But unfortunately,

157
00:28:56,781 --> 00:29:01,381
it's been confirmed that
we've been infiltrated too.

158
00:29:03,701 --> 00:29:06,341
And that Phantom

159
00:29:09,741 --> 00:29:11,381
is in this room.

160
00:29:22,301 --> 00:29:23,901
Last chance.

161
00:29:24,341 --> 00:29:27,981
Jan 10 12:00pm,
Kyungsung Public Hall.

162
00:29:29,221 --> 00:29:31,021
Governor-General's
inauguration ceremony.

163
00:29:32,261 --> 00:29:37,261
All agents are to turn
up at the inauguration

164
00:29:37,341 --> 00:29:39,821
...to kill the new Governor-General.

165
00:29:42,861 --> 00:29:45,661
There were messages about
Jan 11 and 12

166
00:29:45,701 --> 00:29:49,181
with a couple more venues but

167
00:29:49,781 --> 00:29:53,221
'Jan 10, Kyungsung Public Hall.'

168
00:29:54,101 --> 00:29:58,941
Only this message was coded
in the Shadow Corps' unique style.

169
00:30:00,621 --> 00:30:03,621
And only you five have had
access to this message.

170
00:30:04,621 --> 00:30:10,341
It's no use denying.

171
00:30:12,581 --> 00:30:14,061
To get to the point,

172
00:30:15,301 --> 00:30:18,181
the inauguration will not happen
at Kyungsung Public Hall.

173
00:30:23,461 --> 00:30:28,981
'All agents to show up.'

174
00:30:32,221 --> 00:30:41,901
But thankfully, it looks like
the entire group will be there

175
00:30:46,301 --> 00:30:48,381
tomorrow!

176
00:30:49,861 --> 00:30:54,821
You are all equally under suspicion.

177
00:30:57,461 --> 00:31:00,141
That suspicion won't go away by itself.

178
00:31:02,301 --> 00:31:03,941
You must either prove yourself clean

179
00:31:05,101 --> 00:31:09,861
or identify the culprit to survive.

180
00:31:12,141 --> 00:31:13,861
I'll give you until noon.

181
00:31:14,221 --> 00:31:16,461
I hope you think wisely.

182
00:31:17,341 --> 00:31:21,181
At noon, I'll start
torturing you one-by-one

183
00:31:22,061 --> 00:31:24,981
in random order to be fair.

184
00:31:25,941 --> 00:31:27,021
That's all for now.

185
00:31:28,661 --> 00:31:33,141
I look forward to your cooperation.

186
00:31:42,221 --> 00:31:43,461
I'll show you to your room.

187
00:32:10,621 --> 00:32:11,821
Are you trying to get yourself killed?

188
00:32:12,661 --> 00:32:14,381
This is fuel storage.

189
00:32:16,981 --> 00:32:18,741
No smoking!

190
00:32:21,421 --> 00:32:22,901
Is that right?

191
00:32:25,501 --> 00:32:29,581
Sure you lost it in the car?

192
00:32:30,501 --> 00:32:33,341
It's gotta be there somewhere.
Look again.

193
00:32:34,381 --> 00:32:37,341
This wouldn't have happened
if you had let me pack.

194
00:33:04,061 --> 00:33:05,261
Is this it?

195
00:33:07,461 --> 00:33:09,621
There you are.

196
00:34:21,781 --> 00:34:25,221
A shared room?
Are they kidding me?

197
00:34:25,461 --> 00:34:26,821
I'll rip their heads off.

198
00:34:26,981 --> 00:34:28,581
Pretend I'm not here,
I'll do the same.

199
00:34:30,781 --> 00:34:31,701
Light.

200
00:34:38,301 --> 00:34:39,221
I said light.

201
00:35:13,661 --> 00:35:15,061
The damned phone is dead!

202
00:35:18,061 --> 00:35:20,301
Get out.

203
00:35:22,861 --> 00:35:24,741
Can't you hear? I said get out.

204
00:35:26,661 --> 00:35:27,941
Are you deaf?

205
00:35:27,941 --> 00:35:30,381
Get your hands off me
before I break them.

206
00:35:32,301 --> 00:35:34,301
Relax, bitch.

207
00:35:36,021 --> 00:35:39,261
Fine, just give me a moment.
I need to change.

208
00:35:41,221 --> 00:35:43,581
I said I need to get changed.

209
00:35:44,061 --> 00:35:47,341
Don't be shy.
Removing clothes is your second nature.

210
00:35:48,461 --> 00:35:50,661
What an unbelievable bitch you are!

211
00:36:33,421 --> 00:36:37,261
You wanted to see me, Murayama?

212
00:36:39,381 --> 00:36:42,941
This doesn't come as a surprise.

213
00:36:45,061 --> 00:36:48,061
Ever since I heard
you were coming to Kyungsung,

214
00:36:48,581 --> 00:36:53,301
I knew you'd have it out with me
one way or another.

215
00:36:55,661 --> 00:36:58,501
Let's cut to the chase.
This Phantom...

216
00:36:59,261 --> 00:37:01,781
Don't waste your time trying.

217
00:37:01,941 --> 00:37:05,661
You don't have what it takes.

218
00:37:09,621 --> 00:37:11,261
The Phantom is mine.

219
00:37:17,701 --> 00:37:18,861
In return,

220
00:37:20,021 --> 00:37:26,461
you'll pay for the humiliation
you have brought upon me.

221
00:37:48,181 --> 00:37:50,101
Gold Theater

222
00:38:07,901 --> 00:38:08,781
You.

223
00:38:10,221 --> 00:38:12,381
I'm going to Kyungsung now,

224
00:38:12,461 --> 00:38:15,261
and the first thing I'm going to do
is sack you.

225
00:39:11,261 --> 00:39:12,301
What the...?

226
00:39:15,301 --> 00:39:19,141
You snuck up silent as a mouse.

227
00:39:23,541 --> 00:39:24,941
I came to ask you something.

228
00:39:26,541 --> 00:39:29,981
What can you hope to learn
when I know nothing?

229
00:39:31,661 --> 00:39:35,981
Earlier, in the dining room,
you were talking about Park

230
00:39:37,701 --> 00:39:40,941
and said she's different
from the rest of us.

231
00:39:42,741 --> 00:39:43,861
What did you mean by that?

232
00:39:44,541 --> 00:39:48,781
You really don't know?

233
00:39:52,181 --> 00:39:54,541
It's an open secret.

234
00:39:56,261 --> 00:40:00,181
Park's father bought a plane
for the former Governor-General.

235
00:40:01,261 --> 00:40:05,661
Even the Japan acknowledges
her family's wealth.

236
00:40:07,261 --> 00:40:09,861
I thought she might know
something we don't.

237
00:40:10,341 --> 00:40:12,581
Or heard something at her home.

238
00:40:15,861 --> 00:40:19,821
You have an idea about
who the Phantom might be?

239
00:40:21,661 --> 00:40:24,301
It's clear the Phantom is among us.

240
00:40:26,381 --> 00:40:27,861
Bring me a phone!

241
00:40:27,901 --> 00:40:29,661
You better stay in your place.

242
00:40:30,301 --> 00:40:32,381
You pigs bring it to me when I say so!

243
00:40:33,221 --> 00:40:35,461
Return to your room at once.

244
00:40:36,421 --> 00:40:39,261
Shut up and bring me a phone!

245
00:40:39,301 --> 00:40:43,381
What's gotten into her?

246
00:40:44,061 --> 00:40:45,101
I'll take a look.

247
00:41:02,661 --> 00:41:03,581
There's no one here.

248
00:41:06,821 --> 00:41:08,181
I want to ask you something.

249
00:41:11,861 --> 00:41:12,941
That day...

250
00:41:25,141 --> 00:41:27,981
We'll put a tap on Park and Baekho.

251
00:41:31,581 --> 00:41:34,101
Once I make that call,
you're all good as dead.

252
00:41:34,141 --> 00:41:35,221
You sons of bitches!

253
00:41:51,461 --> 00:41:53,541
Get me the Deputy Governor-General.

254
00:41:54,581 --> 00:41:58,861
I know you're listening to this,
so cut the crap and connect me!

255
00:42:10,341 --> 00:42:12,181
Hello.

256
00:42:13,421 --> 00:42:14,341
Who the hell are you?

257
00:42:14,541 --> 00:42:17,501
This is Ayanami,
secretary to the Deputy Governor.

258
00:42:17,621 --> 00:42:21,101
Who are you kidding?
I'm the Deputy's secretary!

259
00:42:21,261 --> 00:42:23,101
How dare they replace me!

260
00:42:23,541 --> 00:42:25,141
Don't you dare fuck me over!

261
00:42:25,221 --> 00:42:26,661
The same to you, fucking bitch!

262
00:42:26,981 --> 00:42:28,461
Good day, then.

263
00:42:30,941 --> 00:42:32,781
Hello? Hello?

264
00:42:32,901 --> 00:42:34,541
Bitch!

265
00:42:38,341 --> 00:42:39,261
Go on.

266
00:42:39,941 --> 00:42:41,621
Calm down.

267
00:42:41,661 --> 00:42:42,461
Don't touch me.

268
00:42:42,501 --> 00:42:43,181
Just shut up.

269
00:42:43,221 --> 00:42:44,101
Out of my way!

270
00:42:51,981 --> 00:42:53,981
They have wires everywhere,

271
00:42:54,701 --> 00:42:57,501
recording everything we say.

272
00:43:05,541 --> 00:43:07,061
You have something to ask me?

273
00:43:15,301 --> 00:43:16,421
Hana...

274
00:43:17,901 --> 00:43:20,101
Wait for me, baby...

275
00:43:20,821 --> 00:43:23,621
Wiretap report

276
00:43:24,581 --> 00:43:25,741
Do you trust him?

277
00:43:26,861 --> 00:43:27,661
Sir?

278
00:43:30,261 --> 00:43:33,181
Do you trust Murayama?

279
00:43:34,981 --> 00:43:37,141
Of course, sir.

280
00:43:37,981 --> 00:43:39,981
I trust Murayama.

281
00:43:47,821 --> 00:43:50,181
The former Chief Guard
Murayama Toshio

282
00:43:50,901 --> 00:43:53,581
killed himself without leaving a note.

283
00:43:54,941 --> 00:43:58,541
Murayama Jr. lost all his
professional advantages like that,

284
00:43:58,581 --> 00:44:00,421
and has since been demoted.

285
00:44:04,781 --> 00:44:08,221
That's all you know?

286
00:44:23,701 --> 00:44:24,701
Murayama!

287
00:44:32,181 --> 00:44:33,381
Murayama Junji!

288
00:44:35,501 --> 00:44:39,901
The appointment to Shanghai
was supposed to be yours,

289
00:44:39,941 --> 00:44:43,301
but Takahara took the post
at the last minute.

290
00:44:43,341 --> 00:44:47,261
I wasn't happy but complied,
and it turns out...

291
00:44:48,621 --> 00:44:51,141
You're of Korean blood?

292
00:44:52,981 --> 00:44:58,861
What was the blood I saw that day?

293
00:45:01,261 --> 00:45:03,381
Anyone can make up an excuse
to that question.

294
00:45:04,661 --> 00:45:06,661
That's not what you want to know.

295
00:45:10,341 --> 00:45:12,501
Are you the Phantom?

296
00:45:17,541 --> 00:45:18,821
Please say no.

297
00:45:22,101 --> 00:45:23,221
Chakyung!

298
00:45:28,181 --> 00:45:29,261
Are you the Phantom?

299
00:45:33,461 --> 00:45:35,781
I beg you, Baekho...

300
00:45:40,461 --> 00:45:41,501
Save yourself.

301
00:45:50,941 --> 00:45:53,621
I've always liked you.

302
00:45:56,741 --> 00:45:57,821
I know.

303
00:45:58,621 --> 00:46:02,061
My mother was the only Korean
in my entire family.

304
00:46:03,021 --> 00:46:04,341
That small fact

305
00:46:05,581 --> 00:46:09,621
doesn't change the entire line
of blood I've inherited.

306
00:46:12,941 --> 00:46:14,781
7th generation of
the Murayama family.

307
00:46:15,381 --> 00:46:20,861
The promising, elite heir
born in Kyungsung, fluent in Korean.

308
00:46:21,461 --> 00:46:23,221
Where does the lie begin?

309
00:46:25,141 --> 00:46:26,621
Answer me, fraud!

310
00:46:32,301 --> 00:46:38,141
The fact that I'm born of
a Korean mother changes me?

311
00:46:39,181 --> 00:46:40,781
Do you want to deny me?

312
00:46:41,141 --> 00:46:43,901
As long as Korean blood
flows in your veins,

313
00:46:45,101 --> 00:46:48,341
you're nothing more than
one of the suspects.

314
00:46:49,381 --> 00:46:52,981
You'll have to prove
you're not the Phantom.

315
00:46:55,381 --> 00:46:58,181
To Kyungsung! Now!

316
00:47:02,461 --> 00:47:03,741
You pathetic scum.

317
00:47:04,581 --> 00:47:06,661
You were lingering around
like a dog in heat

318
00:47:06,741 --> 00:47:10,381
wanting to be like me.
So I took you under my wing.

319
00:47:11,021 --> 00:47:12,541
And now, you want to bite me?

320
00:47:13,341 --> 00:47:16,741
Fine! Doubt all you want.

321
00:47:17,621 --> 00:47:21,541
You'll end up paying for it.

322
00:47:34,661 --> 00:47:35,421
Get him!

323
00:47:42,221 --> 00:47:45,261
This is a final warning.
Get out of the car.

324
00:47:45,901 --> 00:47:48,501
This is my final order.
Start the car.

325
00:47:52,821 --> 00:47:55,101
You can't shoot me.

326
00:47:56,461 --> 00:47:57,381
Why not?

327
00:48:00,221 --> 00:48:02,861
I could be the Phantom.

328
00:48:02,901 --> 00:48:05,141
What's stopping you?
Shoot her!

329
00:48:05,741 --> 00:48:06,861
You're not so sure now.

330
00:48:07,741 --> 00:48:09,341
You don't have the balls.

331
00:48:09,781 --> 00:48:12,181
Do you have what it takes?

332
00:48:20,101 --> 00:48:23,701
I didn't use a gun or a knife
when I killed my mother.

333
00:48:24,461 --> 00:48:28,781
Strangling out the last drop of
her insolent blood,

334
00:48:31,501 --> 00:48:32,861
I stopped her breath.

335
00:48:36,941 --> 00:48:40,741
There's no ground for denying
the legitimacy of my blood.

336
00:48:41,501 --> 00:48:45,701
If you plan on continuing
to defame me,

337
00:48:46,781 --> 00:48:47,741
remember.

338
00:48:48,861 --> 00:48:52,021
I will use neither
gun nor knife with you.

339
00:48:55,461 --> 00:48:56,541
Wait and see.

340
00:48:56,861 --> 00:48:58,621
I'm catching the Phantom
before sundown.

341
00:49:04,261 --> 00:49:05,941
Stay clear of Murayama from now on.

342
00:49:08,541 --> 00:49:11,781
Get your act together.
Look at me!

343
00:49:13,301 --> 00:49:15,501
No one will suspect or interrogate you.

344
00:49:15,581 --> 00:49:17,741
Everything will be settled
before the end of the day.

345
00:49:17,781 --> 00:49:20,061
You gotta stick it out, okay?

346
00:49:22,781 --> 00:49:26,581
Alright, alright!
Get the fuck off me!

347
00:49:36,221 --> 00:49:40,021
You're not stupid, are you?

348
00:49:41,661 --> 00:49:45,421
I'm disappointed in you, Miss Yuriko.

349
00:49:46,021 --> 00:49:47,141
Think about it.

350
00:49:48,141 --> 00:49:51,781
Could I bring you here
without the Deputy knowing?

351
00:49:52,541 --> 00:49:54,901
It was his idea.

352
00:49:55,781 --> 00:49:59,821
He wanted to check you out
because you were his bitch.

353
00:50:00,821 --> 00:50:01,821
Do you understand?

354
00:50:04,701 --> 00:50:09,541
Your time was up.

355
00:50:18,781 --> 00:50:20,341
Let go of me.

356
00:50:44,701 --> 00:50:45,701
Poor Hana...

357
00:50:49,621 --> 00:50:50,981
You must be starving.

358
00:50:55,821 --> 00:50:57,261
Hang in there.

359
00:50:58,941 --> 00:51:00,341
I'll be home soon, darling.

360
00:51:01,501 --> 00:51:02,701
Hana...

361
00:51:56,901 --> 00:51:58,941
Who should be called in first?

362
00:52:00,061 --> 00:52:03,101
There are two types of commanders.

363
00:52:04,301 --> 00:52:06,621
One goes for the prime suspect
right away.

364
00:52:07,101 --> 00:52:10,901
The other starts with the witness
who knows the secret.

365
00:52:12,901 --> 00:52:16,261
The former is fast,
the latter cautious.

366
00:52:20,221 --> 00:52:21,781
Which do you think I am?

367
00:52:34,581 --> 00:52:35,581
Hey!

368
00:52:36,461 --> 00:52:40,781
Don't walk around
without permission!

369
00:53:04,101 --> 00:53:04,981
You...

370
00:53:09,061 --> 00:53:12,061
I couldn't care less who the Phantom is,

371
00:53:12,101 --> 00:53:14,781
but right now,
I would like it to be you.

372
00:53:15,981 --> 00:53:18,061
You'll see what I mean.

373
00:53:20,581 --> 00:53:24,821
And you will live.
Your eyes say you won't go easily.

374
00:53:28,061 --> 00:53:29,021
Hey!

375
00:53:53,341 --> 00:53:56,501
Lost something?
Serves you right, bitch.

376
00:54:04,781 --> 00:54:06,941
Report every movement
the suspects make.

377
00:55:13,461 --> 00:55:15,621
You!
Where are you going?

378
00:55:16,821 --> 00:55:19,941
I... have to check something.

379
00:55:19,981 --> 00:55:23,861
I can't tell you what it is.
But I have to go.

380
00:55:25,261 --> 00:55:30,141
It's past 12:00! There's no time.
I've got to go now, right now!

381
00:55:30,181 --> 00:55:31,741
Return to your room.

382
00:55:31,941 --> 00:55:32,781
Don't try to stop me.

383
00:55:34,301 --> 00:55:35,381
Let him go.

384
00:55:40,901 --> 00:55:42,021
I said let me go!

385
00:55:46,341 --> 00:55:47,421
Thank you!

386
00:56:04,221 --> 00:56:06,141
Yuriko darling, no one's here, right?

387
00:56:53,621 --> 00:56:57,861
I'll be honest with you.
You're here as a formality.

388
00:56:59,781 --> 00:57:04,261
I could've let you go
see your mother.

389
00:57:04,741 --> 00:57:07,861
You're all she's got.

390
00:57:10,861 --> 00:57:13,501
You could walk free right now.

391
00:57:14,301 --> 00:57:19,501
But if you keep quiet,
you become a party to the crime.

392
00:57:22,101 --> 00:57:23,421
Why take the risk?

393
00:57:28,981 --> 00:57:34,141
Tell me what you know,
and you'll walk free.

394
00:57:36,821 --> 00:57:38,021
Who is the Phantom?

395
00:58:19,781 --> 00:58:22,901
You'd better not waste any more time.

396
00:58:27,581 --> 00:58:28,381
I...

397
00:58:32,541 --> 00:58:33,741
have no idea.

398
00:58:36,821 --> 00:58:38,141
You don't know.

399
00:58:44,101 --> 00:58:46,181
See?

400
00:58:47,181 --> 00:58:50,021
These cards are supposed to
tell me who the phantom is.

401
00:58:50,381 --> 00:58:52,101
They've never once been wrong.

402
00:58:52,981 --> 00:58:53,901
But...

403
00:58:54,981 --> 00:58:56,661
But what?
Who does it say it is?

404
00:58:58,341 --> 00:58:59,181
Me.

405
00:59:00,181 --> 00:59:02,861
I'm really not!
But they point to me every time.

406
00:59:04,221 --> 00:59:06,061
What do you think?

407
00:59:09,661 --> 00:59:11,701
I don't think it's you either.

408
00:59:12,341 --> 00:59:17,461
Really? Why not?

409
00:59:19,181 --> 00:59:24,301
If the Shadow Corps had a brain,
they wouldn't give the job to anyone.

410
00:59:27,701 --> 00:59:28,741
Huh...?

411
01:00:09,261 --> 01:00:10,461
Well, thanks anyway.

412
01:00:10,901 --> 01:00:13,821
Please tell them it's not me.

413
01:00:14,421 --> 01:00:16,941
I have to be home by tomorrow.

414
01:00:17,341 --> 01:00:20,261
My baby is starving,
waiting for me to come home.

415
01:00:21,021 --> 01:00:21,941
Please.

416
01:00:22,261 --> 01:00:23,501
Cheon.

417
01:00:27,381 --> 01:00:28,661
Come in here.

418
01:00:39,901 --> 01:00:40,941
Park Chakyung!

419
01:01:10,781 --> 01:01:11,781
You saw it, right?

420
01:01:13,541 --> 01:01:15,541
Murayama going all crazy
and shooting at me.

421
01:01:17,261 --> 01:01:20,061
I was shocked to see him
completely overreact

422
01:01:20,221 --> 01:01:24,421
in front of everyone, no less

423
01:01:25,861 --> 01:01:27,541
as if trying to show them.

424
01:01:29,021 --> 01:01:34,301
He was trying to prove
that he isn't the Phantom.

425
01:01:35,421 --> 01:01:36,461
What?

426
01:01:37,421 --> 01:01:38,261
He can't be...

427
01:01:40,301 --> 01:01:41,141
Right?

428
01:01:42,181 --> 01:01:43,981
That's what I thought too

429
01:01:44,781 --> 01:01:46,901
but when I came back to my room,

430
01:01:47,301 --> 01:01:49,701
I found out Murayama
had snuck into my room.

431
01:01:51,461 --> 01:01:54,141
You know what I found after he left?

432
01:02:19,621 --> 01:02:20,901
That's enough, Park.

433
01:02:42,781 --> 01:02:45,421
He had planted it in Park's suitcase.

434
01:02:47,421 --> 01:02:50,061
Murayama had it on him
which means...

435
01:02:51,221 --> 01:02:52,421
He is the Phantom.

436
01:02:55,421 --> 01:02:58,341
And he was trying to frame Park
with the evidence.

437
01:03:00,381 --> 01:03:04,141
You're right!
He snuck into my room, too!

438
01:03:04,821 --> 01:03:09,461
If I hadn't caught him,
he'd have framed me instead! Fuck!

439
01:03:09,621 --> 01:03:11,621
Fuck, right!
That sneaky bastard!

440
01:03:12,101 --> 01:03:13,821
Take the evidence and report him.

441
01:03:13,821 --> 01:03:16,541
It could even lead to your promotion.

442
01:03:17,901 --> 01:03:20,021
I thought about doing it myself...

443
01:03:21,021 --> 01:03:24,141
Why didn't you?
It's such a good chance.

444
01:03:24,741 --> 01:03:27,461
It's just how I feel.

445
01:03:32,181 --> 01:03:33,341
Yuriko darling!

446
01:03:41,061 --> 01:03:42,141
What?

447
01:03:43,261 --> 01:03:44,581
Let's all just go home, okay?

448
01:03:47,141 --> 01:03:48,101
Okay!

449
01:04:21,621 --> 01:04:23,981
Informer
Cheon Eunho

450
01:04:31,181 --> 01:04:33,261
What that is is...

451
01:04:35,261 --> 01:04:39,981
Take it to the Chief Guard.
He'll know what it is.

452
01:04:40,061 --> 01:04:43,981
Careful! Ink's not dry yet.

453
01:04:53,301 --> 01:04:58,221
No one can hear us now.

454
01:04:59,661 --> 01:05:01,141
Listen carefully, Park.

455
01:05:04,621 --> 01:05:06,101
I'm the Phantom.

456
01:05:07,301 --> 01:05:08,381
And I know

457
01:05:09,741 --> 01:05:11,341
that you're a Phantom, too.

458
01:05:12,741 --> 01:05:17,381
You'd already know
it's impossible to get out by yourself.

459
01:05:18,581 --> 01:05:20,341
We need to work together.

460
01:05:20,701 --> 01:05:24,861
In order to do that, I need to be sure.

461
01:05:27,101 --> 01:05:29,941
Tell me, Park.

462
01:05:32,781 --> 01:05:33,981
Are you a Phantom?

463
01:06:55,181 --> 01:06:56,061
What the hell?

464
01:06:56,821 --> 01:06:57,861
What are you doing?

465
01:07:34,141 --> 01:07:35,301
Are you crazy?

466
01:07:36,421 --> 01:07:37,621
What the fuck's going on!

467
01:07:41,341 --> 01:07:42,781
Jan 8

468
01:07:43,381 --> 01:07:45,221
6:00pm, Gold Theater...

469
01:07:49,221 --> 01:07:51,541
Exactly when I was
looking around the theater.

470
01:07:53,461 --> 01:07:54,581
You managed to avoid me.

471
01:07:56,301 --> 01:07:58,381
Is this where
your intuition misled you?

472
01:07:59,341 --> 01:08:01,341
Intuition can't beat solid evidence.

473
01:08:03,861 --> 01:08:06,821
Don't ask me, ask yourself.

474
01:08:07,501 --> 01:08:08,061
Takahara,

475
01:08:09,421 --> 01:08:11,581
do you truly believe
that I'm the Phantom?

476
01:08:14,061 --> 01:08:15,061
Is that right?

477
01:08:16,581 --> 01:08:17,741
Now that I hear it,

478
01:08:19,021 --> 01:08:21,861
that question isn't for me.

479
01:09:03,781 --> 01:09:05,261
Why did you help me?

480
01:09:14,381 --> 01:09:16,861
Is that what you think?

481
01:09:19,901 --> 01:09:21,901
You could've reported me.

482
01:09:24,021 --> 01:09:26,301
You think the world
revolves around you?

483
01:09:26,901 --> 01:09:32,501
Help you? No.
This is between me and Murayama.

484
01:09:49,781 --> 01:09:52,181
I name Murayama as the Phantom.

485
01:09:53,581 --> 01:09:54,781
Do you have any objections?

486
01:09:55,341 --> 01:10:00,021
If you say nothing,
that in itself is a clear answer.

487
01:10:01,581 --> 01:10:06,341
We'll conclude that it's Murayama
and close the investigation.

488
01:10:13,101 --> 01:10:17,221
It looks like your mother arrived
in the hospital just in time.

489
01:10:22,541 --> 01:10:25,301
I don't know if you're aware,

490
01:10:26,101 --> 01:10:28,261
but you have given your answer
to this question, too.

491
01:10:28,781 --> 01:10:31,341
A clear one.

492
01:10:32,541 --> 01:10:33,221
Kill her.

493
01:10:33,701 --> 01:10:34,461
No!

494
01:10:35,581 --> 01:10:38,461
I'm sorry, I'm so sorry.

495
01:10:38,501 --> 01:10:40,381
Please spare my mother.

496
01:10:40,421 --> 01:10:45,061
I'm sorry. I beg you!

497
01:10:45,981 --> 01:10:47,501
Hold.

498
01:10:47,661 --> 01:10:50,541
I'm sorry.

499
01:10:58,381 --> 01:11:00,181
Now we can begin the discussion.

500
01:11:00,861 --> 01:11:02,941
I'll ask you for the last time.

501
01:11:05,181 --> 01:11:08,141
Who is the Phantom?

502
01:11:22,381 --> 01:11:24,221
It's Park Chakyung.

503
01:12:39,941 --> 01:12:45,381
How was your long day, everyone?

504
01:12:47,861 --> 01:12:50,221
I did quite a bit of legwork,

505
01:12:51,941 --> 01:12:57,021
and eventually found one witness
and one piece of evidence.

506
01:12:58,701 --> 01:13:01,541
What's funny is that

507
01:13:03,101 --> 01:13:05,661
each points to a different suspect.

508
01:13:07,501 --> 01:13:10,981
The evidence points to Murayama,

509
01:13:12,541 --> 01:13:15,621
the witness points to Park.

510
01:13:17,141 --> 01:13:20,101
To be honest,

511
01:13:21,181 --> 01:13:24,701
I've had enough discussion
about the evidence.

512
01:13:26,781 --> 01:13:33,061
I'd now like to verify
the witness's testimony.

513
01:13:33,861 --> 01:13:37,901
I'm talking about you,

514
01:13:43,741 --> 01:13:45,061
Park Chakyung.

515
01:13:46,901 --> 01:13:49,941
If you're the Phantom,
as the witness says...

516
01:13:52,661 --> 01:13:53,501
Look.

517
01:13:54,141 --> 01:13:58,261
They're in boiling water
because of you.

518
01:14:00,541 --> 01:14:02,541
Relieve them of their suffering.

519
01:14:04,301 --> 01:14:05,781
Give us an answer, Park.

520
01:14:06,101 --> 01:14:07,581
Are you the Phantom?

521
01:14:11,181 --> 01:14:12,181
Fine.

522
01:14:14,981 --> 01:14:18,221
Let's talk about him instead.

523
01:14:20,741 --> 01:14:22,621
What's this young man's crime?

524
01:14:24,101 --> 01:14:30,461
He put his own life at risk
and did his best

525
01:14:32,141 --> 01:14:35,741
to protect you, Park.

526
01:14:40,101 --> 01:14:42,141
Now you must answer this question.

527
01:14:42,821 --> 01:14:45,581
What can you do for him in return?

528
01:14:46,501 --> 01:14:48,021
What will you put on stake?

529
01:14:48,661 --> 01:14:49,901
Answer me, Park!

530
01:14:50,701 --> 01:14:53,581
Will you be a coward?
To the end?

531
01:14:53,781 --> 01:14:58,781
What will do you for this boy
who risked everything for you?

532
01:14:58,821 --> 01:15:00,901
What can you do? Say it!

533
01:15:07,741 --> 01:15:09,021
That's a shame.

534
01:15:23,701 --> 01:15:27,741
You haven't eaten all day, have you?

535
01:15:32,621 --> 01:15:35,381
Please, dig in.

536
01:16:46,461 --> 01:16:47,381
You...!

537
01:16:48,141 --> 01:16:49,501
Ready, aim!

538
01:16:55,101 --> 01:16:56,141
Hold your fire.

539
01:16:59,861 --> 01:17:01,061
Now!

540
01:17:19,941 --> 01:17:23,381
Murayama, you're the Phantom!

541
01:17:23,621 --> 01:17:27,861
We all know,
so you'd better come clean.

542
01:17:28,781 --> 01:17:30,141
Lower your gun.

543
01:17:30,581 --> 01:17:31,741
You may be a Phantom,

544
01:17:33,021 --> 01:17:36,821
but surely you can't sacrifice the life
of an innocent person!

545
01:17:39,421 --> 01:17:42,941
Give me a gun! Quickly!

546
01:17:54,781 --> 01:17:55,821
I...

547
01:17:56,901 --> 01:18:00,781
...need to be home
more than anyone in the world.

548
01:18:02,101 --> 01:18:05,661
I'll kill anyone who gets in the way.

549
01:19:10,581 --> 01:19:11,501
Yuriko!

550
01:19:13,821 --> 01:19:16,181
Don't die yet, Miss Yuriko.

551
01:20:04,181 --> 01:20:05,381
Get her!

552
01:20:12,781 --> 01:20:14,541
I'm sorry.

553
01:20:14,981 --> 01:20:17,101
Don't apologize, Baekho.

554
01:20:19,221 --> 01:20:22,061
You don't owe me anything.

555
01:20:49,541 --> 01:20:51,141
Get ready.

556
01:20:57,861 --> 01:20:58,781
Not here!

557
01:20:58,941 --> 01:21:00,141
No one here, either.

558
01:21:42,981 --> 01:21:43,981
Father...

559
01:21:46,661 --> 01:21:48,021
I did it.

560
01:21:51,741 --> 01:21:52,941
Why?

561
01:21:53,941 --> 01:21:55,981
I was afraid this would go on.

562
01:22:06,861 --> 01:22:10,061
Are you crazy? Why...

563
01:22:11,741 --> 01:22:12,861
Why did you do it?

564
01:22:14,021 --> 01:22:16,781
For Joseon?

565
01:22:20,421 --> 01:22:21,821
For your country?

566
01:22:26,301 --> 01:22:29,581
What is that? What is Joseon?

567
01:22:31,301 --> 01:22:32,861
What the hell is that...!

568
01:22:52,341 --> 01:22:53,501
Junji...

569
01:23:07,141 --> 01:23:10,581
The sounds of the river never
silence the regrets of fallen heroes.

570
01:23:12,061 --> 01:23:14,621
Only after the coldest night

571
01:23:14,701 --> 01:23:18,061
does the green of the
evergreen look brighter.

572
01:23:31,381 --> 01:23:32,341
Who are you?

573
01:23:36,061 --> 01:23:37,141
Tell me you who are!

574
01:23:40,141 --> 01:23:42,541
I'm going to save you with my life.

575
01:23:44,221 --> 01:23:46,821
You'll get out of here and
save our comrades with your life.

576
01:23:48,741 --> 01:23:50,381
I will finish up here.

577
01:23:51,141 --> 01:23:53,461
Don't think I'm helping you.

578
01:23:54,061 --> 01:23:56,021
We're all doing what we can.

579
01:24:02,421 --> 01:24:04,221
You... what are you?

580
01:24:07,341 --> 01:24:09,421
There are only two bullets left,
use them well.

581
01:24:10,221 --> 01:24:12,501
Are you saying
there are two Phantoms?

582
01:24:13,581 --> 01:24:17,661
Someone like you, no less?

583
01:24:39,861 --> 01:24:42,141
I got these scars when
I was tortured in Manchuria.

584
01:24:45,141 --> 01:24:47,861
When I first took off my clothes
in front of the Deputy,

585
01:24:48,781 --> 01:24:52,381
I told him they were self-inflicted,
and he loved it,

586
01:24:53,341 --> 01:24:54,821
sick pervert...

587
01:24:57,381 --> 01:24:59,901
But his perversion made it easier
for me to serve my country.

588
01:25:08,661 --> 01:25:11,261
Here are the scars I got
from the Deputy.

589
01:25:16,141 --> 01:25:18,301
Up to here are
from the first winter...

590
01:25:19,821 --> 01:25:21,701
And from the following spring.

591
01:25:25,861 --> 01:25:27,901
Every time he burned my skin,

592
01:25:29,541 --> 01:25:34,101
'I'm dead, I'm dead.'
I said to myself, over and over.

593
01:25:46,621 --> 01:25:48,421
There's nothing left for me
in this world.

594
01:25:51,741 --> 01:25:53,141
It's okay if I die.

595
01:26:16,381 --> 01:26:17,621
Sir...

596
01:26:37,061 --> 01:26:43,141
One must judge people based on
experience, not reputation.

597
01:26:44,021 --> 01:26:45,301
This is your last chance.

598
01:26:46,501 --> 01:26:48,301
Don't disappoint me again.

599
01:26:53,221 --> 01:26:54,781
I'm sorry, sir.

600
01:26:55,701 --> 01:26:59,021
Do whatever you have to.

601
01:26:59,181 --> 01:27:01,101
Just don't get in my way.

602
01:27:03,581 --> 01:27:06,381
I had no idea they'd planted
two Phantoms in the government.

603
01:27:06,941 --> 01:27:11,581
Me neither.
A backup just in case?

604
01:27:11,901 --> 01:27:16,701
Or, to help the other out
in case of trouble.

605
01:27:23,021 --> 01:27:24,421
Live.

606
01:27:27,221 --> 01:27:29,661
Die only when your time comes.

607
01:27:36,821 --> 01:27:37,981
Keep searching.

608
01:27:43,941 --> 01:27:45,221
We gotta move now.

609
01:27:45,621 --> 01:27:49,581
We have to cut the comms line
and buy time until dawn.

610
01:27:51,741 --> 01:27:54,621
With this size of military,
there's gotta be an armory.

611
01:27:55,981 --> 01:27:58,421
I scouted the premises inside out,
but didn't find any.

612
01:27:59,341 --> 01:28:01,741
The only place left is the basement.

613
01:28:04,661 --> 01:28:09,461
To the left of the gate is a fuel storage.
It will come in handy.

614
01:28:09,821 --> 01:28:11,901
In the corner is a small garage.

615
01:28:12,621 --> 01:28:17,261
There is a civilian car inside.

616
01:28:19,461 --> 01:28:24,661
Secure the vehicle and weapons,
and we can make it to Kyungsung.

617
01:28:42,341 --> 01:28:44,861
Here's the comms line and electricity.

618
01:28:45,301 --> 01:28:46,501
I'll take the comms.

619
01:28:58,741 --> 01:29:00,181
This'll soak up petrol well.

620
01:29:16,261 --> 01:29:18,421
It'll make it easier to run.

621
01:29:35,781 --> 01:29:37,621
We haven't exchanged names yet.

622
01:29:37,861 --> 01:29:41,341
I'm Park Chakyung
from Kyungsung.

623
01:29:41,981 --> 01:29:44,861
Why bother?

624
01:30:11,061 --> 01:30:13,541
Fire!

625
01:30:19,901 --> 01:30:20,981
The engine room.

626
01:30:21,701 --> 01:30:23,821
- Get the fire extinguisher!
- Yes, sir!

627
01:30:25,701 --> 01:30:27,501
Hurry!

628
01:30:27,541 --> 01:30:29,101
It's the engine room.

629
01:30:39,821 --> 01:30:41,021
Are you alright, sir?

630
01:30:45,341 --> 01:30:49,061
You can't search this tiny little hotel?

631
01:30:50,781 --> 01:30:56,981
Catch them before dawn, or I'll kill you
for failing to follow orders.

632
01:30:58,181 --> 01:30:59,461
Follow me.

633
01:31:09,741 --> 01:31:11,021
Upstairs is the hotel.

634
01:31:12,141 --> 01:31:15,741
They'll have it for all the buildings.

635
01:31:30,541 --> 01:31:31,221
I'll take the top.

636
01:31:36,861 --> 01:31:38,301
Three, two...

637
01:31:59,461 --> 01:32:03,861
It's too dangerous to go back out.
There's gotta be a way out.

638
01:32:36,941 --> 01:32:38,901
This way is the ocean.
Should be safer.

639
01:32:47,021 --> 01:32:47,821
Shush!

640
01:33:00,181 --> 01:33:01,621
You go first and pull me up.

641
01:33:10,101 --> 01:33:10,781
What...?

642
01:33:10,821 --> 01:33:11,741
Quiet.

643
01:33:20,981 --> 01:33:22,181
Don't be stupid!

644
01:33:26,381 --> 01:33:27,101
Go.

645
01:33:27,461 --> 01:33:29,461
Come on, you can make it.

646
01:33:31,901 --> 01:33:37,421
My name is Ahn Kangok
from Hamgyong.

647
01:33:40,261 --> 01:33:42,341
Thank you for asking my name.

648
01:33:49,861 --> 01:33:52,421
Get out of here and
save all our comrades.

649
01:33:55,261 --> 01:33:56,541
No!

650
01:34:03,821 --> 01:34:05,541
Who is it? Freeze!

651
01:34:05,781 --> 01:34:07,141
Put your hands up.

652
01:34:08,581 --> 01:34:12,181
I'm Ahn Kangok with the Shadow Corps.
I'm the Phantom.

653
01:34:13,021 --> 01:34:17,661
And... you will never catch me.

654
01:34:29,261 --> 01:34:30,981
Take her to the torture chamber.

655
01:34:52,341 --> 01:34:57,061
Shall we start, Miss Yuriko?

656
01:35:49,661 --> 01:35:52,101
Coordinating with Shanghai to plant

657
01:35:52,301 --> 01:35:57,341
a Phantom in the government...
I'm impressed.

658
01:35:58,221 --> 01:35:59,861
Too bad for you...

659
01:36:01,301 --> 01:36:04,381
We'll always be
anywhere and everywhere.

660
01:36:05,821 --> 01:36:08,141
That sickens me about you.

661
01:36:08,501 --> 01:36:11,421
Your tenacious obsession...

662
01:36:14,341 --> 01:36:19,501
like maggots that relentlessly
hang on to pitiful life in a pool of shit.

663
01:36:20,141 --> 01:36:22,141
You disgusting vermin.

664
01:36:25,861 --> 01:36:27,901
Who is the leader
of the Shadow Corps?

665
01:36:28,581 --> 01:36:29,461
Say it.

666
01:36:42,141 --> 01:36:45,381
Cut off comms and electricity
for isolation,

667
01:36:45,421 --> 01:36:48,341
divert attention by setting fire.

668
01:36:49,261 --> 01:36:51,701
You've been well trained.

669
01:36:56,301 --> 01:36:59,581
Everything's okay,

670
01:37:04,061 --> 01:37:05,941
but they took Yuriko.

671
01:37:07,101 --> 01:37:10,781
Let me save her at least.
I beg you.

672
01:37:11,301 --> 01:37:14,781
It is a pity.

673
01:37:15,821 --> 01:37:18,501
I should have caught
both of you with my bare hands.

674
01:37:19,661 --> 01:37:22,461
It was all going to
come to this eventually.

675
01:37:23,981 --> 01:37:28,701
Couldn't you have just believed me
when I said I was the Phantom?

676
01:37:29,581 --> 01:37:35,421
You're under arrest by the
authority of Police Department.

677
01:37:37,141 --> 01:37:38,301
You know,

678
01:37:41,061 --> 01:37:43,501
I've been wanting to say this.

679
01:37:47,661 --> 01:37:48,381
You...

680
01:37:49,981 --> 01:37:51,461
Shut the fuck up.

681
01:38:14,221 --> 01:38:17,061
The fuel storage has exploded.

682
01:39:34,461 --> 01:39:37,701
I should've come sooner.
I'm sorry.

683
01:39:38,581 --> 01:39:42,141
This is not professional...

684
01:39:43,261 --> 01:39:46,021
Thanks for making me feel less bad.

685
01:39:52,661 --> 01:39:56,101
Takahara, there's no time for this.

686
01:39:56,661 --> 01:39:58,421
We'll lose the Phantoms.

687
01:40:00,421 --> 01:40:05,581
Tenacious bastard...
Korean blood sure flows in your veins.

688
01:40:06,461 --> 01:40:11,981
Of course you're obsessed with blood.

689
01:40:12,701 --> 01:40:14,101
You know why?

690
01:40:15,541 --> 01:40:20,341
Because you're afraid I might
take my place back from you.

691
01:40:20,861 --> 01:40:26,301
You've gotten to where you are
by slandering my reputation.

692
01:40:26,341 --> 01:40:27,461
And you know so well

693
01:40:29,501 --> 01:40:33,021
that you have no power or guts,
nothing on me.

694
01:40:34,381 --> 01:40:35,621
You gonna shoot me?

695
01:40:36,941 --> 01:40:37,941
Go on.

696
01:40:39,101 --> 01:40:41,141
Do it if you dare.

697
01:40:41,221 --> 01:40:42,861
Shut up, Murayama!

698
01:40:45,901 --> 01:40:47,221
Your father

699
01:40:49,981 --> 01:40:52,221
was murdered by your
own Korean mother, right?

700
01:40:54,181 --> 01:40:56,781
A family murdering each other
like animals.

701
01:40:58,021 --> 01:41:00,221
Filthy, lowly blood line.

702
01:41:55,661 --> 01:41:56,901
Mr. Junji...

703
01:41:59,541 --> 01:42:03,261
You said you'd use neither
a gun nor a knife on me.

704
01:43:01,821 --> 01:43:03,901
All the tires have been slashed.

705
01:43:03,941 --> 01:43:04,901
Mechanic!

706
01:43:05,341 --> 01:43:09,181
The Chief Guard's dead.
It's the Phantom's doing.

707
01:43:09,221 --> 01:43:11,701
I told you this was a waste of time.

708
01:43:12,221 --> 01:43:15,461
Morons. Put me on the phone
with the Chief of Police.

709
01:43:20,541 --> 01:43:22,261
Yamada speaking.

710
01:43:22,541 --> 01:43:25,941
Two Phantoms killed the Chief Guard

711
01:43:26,541 --> 01:43:27,901
and ran off to Kyungsung.

712
01:43:28,661 --> 01:43:30,621
It's a race against time.

713
01:43:31,141 --> 01:43:32,661
Before the end of the night,

714
01:43:32,781 --> 01:43:35,421
we must wipe out the Phantoms
and the entire Shadow Corps

715
01:43:36,141 --> 01:43:37,621
or it'll be the end for us.

716
01:43:38,501 --> 01:43:41,101
I will command the field.

717
01:43:50,421 --> 01:43:52,301
No... Wake up.
Open your eyes!

718
01:44:15,941 --> 01:44:20,101
This is an official order
from the Chief of Police.

719
01:44:20,541 --> 01:44:24,261
I will oversee all operations
regarding the emergency situation.

720
01:44:24,781 --> 01:44:28,261
You're all under my command now.

721
01:44:29,021 --> 01:44:29,941
Is that clear?

722
01:44:32,421 --> 01:44:33,261
Is that clear?

723
01:44:56,501 --> 01:44:58,341
Wait up, sweetheart.

724
01:45:03,221 --> 01:45:07,421
I'm sorry for intruding.
We're injured...

725
01:45:14,341 --> 01:45:15,621
Take your time.

726
01:46:07,061 --> 01:46:08,981
Why are you helping us?

727
01:46:10,021 --> 01:46:12,901
The traitors don't get hurt.

728
01:46:15,741 --> 01:46:17,141
Only those defending do.

729
01:46:30,861 --> 01:46:35,461
I told them the goal is
to sweep the entire Shadow Corps.

730
01:46:36,021 --> 01:46:39,861
I restricted the attendants to
Koreans to be sure.

731
01:46:43,461 --> 01:46:45,461
It's been made clear that

732
01:46:45,501 --> 01:46:47,661
Park and Yuriko are to be
shot to death immediately.

733
01:46:50,101 --> 01:46:53,661
Neither Park nor Yuriko
is our biggest priority.

734
01:46:54,821 --> 01:46:59,461
There's someone else
we must find first.

735
01:47:08,901 --> 01:47:10,381
Why am I here...?

736
01:47:10,821 --> 01:47:12,701
You should've just left me.

737
01:47:20,261 --> 01:47:21,541
Dumb cow...

738
01:47:29,021 --> 01:47:33,941
Why didn't you just remain in
the comfort of your family wealth?

739
01:47:34,941 --> 01:47:36,181
Why are you doing this?

740
01:47:37,501 --> 01:47:41,141
You don't come across as
the courageous type.

741
01:47:50,301 --> 01:47:54,301
This was a conviction of my lover.
I want to honor it for her.

742
01:47:56,061 --> 01:47:58,901
You've come far enough.
This is where you stop.

743
01:47:59,261 --> 01:48:03,701
Look who's talking.
You can barely breathe.

744
01:48:04,941 --> 01:48:06,381
You have nothing more at stake.

745
01:48:17,061 --> 01:48:18,381
Stubborn cow...

746
01:49:18,861 --> 01:49:20,421
Allow me to introduce myself first.

747
01:49:21,501 --> 01:49:25,581
I'm Murayama Junji
from the Police Department.

748
01:49:28,021 --> 01:49:29,501
I'll get to the point.

749
01:49:29,541 --> 01:49:33,941
No inauguration ceremony
will take place here today.

750
01:49:36,461 --> 01:49:38,941
This is a trap.

751
01:49:59,501 --> 01:50:02,261
I know all seven members of
the Shadow Corps are here,

752
01:50:06,541 --> 01:50:09,061
and you'll all be apprehended.

753
01:50:09,661 --> 01:50:14,061
But I'm going to give you
one last chance

754
01:50:14,341 --> 01:50:15,341
to give yourselves up.

755
01:50:17,021 --> 01:50:17,901
All of you.

756
01:50:22,581 --> 01:50:26,101
I know it's not easy.

757
01:50:26,221 --> 01:50:29,741
You have reputations to preserve,
causes to uphold.

758
01:50:31,381 --> 01:50:36,341
Actually, I only need
five of you to come forward.

759
01:50:36,381 --> 01:50:42,301
I already have two here.

760
01:50:48,061 --> 01:50:51,661
This girl disguised herself
as an employee of this public hall

761
01:50:51,701 --> 01:50:55,661
to gain access for this old man.

762
01:50:55,701 --> 01:51:02,541
The Shadow Corps were supposed to
get their weapons from him.

763
01:51:03,181 --> 01:51:07,181
The objective: to assassinate
the new Governor-General.

764
01:51:12,581 --> 01:51:16,461
But as you see, all your weapons

765
01:51:16,501 --> 01:51:17,701
are in this crate,

766
01:51:20,501 --> 01:51:28,661
which means that you're unarmed.

767
01:51:30,701 --> 01:51:34,461
What's the point of struggling now?

768
01:51:39,741 --> 01:51:41,981
I feel a sense of duty

769
01:51:44,381 --> 01:51:51,021
to open your eyes to the truth
you blindly choose to ignore,

770
01:51:52,821 --> 01:51:55,941
believing there's still hope
for independence,

771
01:51:56,941 --> 01:52:02,781
the stupid notion that
risking your life is the only way

772
01:52:04,301 --> 01:52:05,261
to love your country.

773
01:52:14,181 --> 01:52:21,061
Let's take a step back

774
01:52:23,141 --> 01:52:25,261
and look at this objectively.

775
01:52:31,301 --> 01:52:32,741
Pathetic Koreans.

776
01:52:34,581 --> 01:52:37,061
You do not have a nation to defend!

777
01:52:39,581 --> 01:52:43,821
Your nation perished 10 years ago!
And you're still clutching to its ghost.

778
01:52:45,461 --> 01:52:48,541
Do you believe
you can still do something?

779
01:52:49,501 --> 01:52:54,061
Let bygones be bygones
and move on.

780
01:52:55,221 --> 01:52:59,261
Open your eyes to reality!

781
01:53:01,341 --> 01:53:03,341
Japan and Joseon share one root!

782
01:53:03,861 --> 01:53:07,341
Paint a greater future
as part of a greater nation!

783
01:53:08,061 --> 01:53:09,781
You are subjects of Imperial Japan.

784
01:53:09,821 --> 01:53:12,101
Repay the sovereign with loyalty.

785
01:53:14,861 --> 01:53:16,301
Come out, Shadow Corps!

786
01:53:36,261 --> 01:53:38,181
Don't budge!

787
01:53:42,261 --> 01:53:44,141
It's not your time to die yet.

788
01:53:49,061 --> 01:53:50,101
Stick it out.

789
01:53:57,741 --> 01:53:58,861
Come on out!

790
01:54:04,861 --> 01:54:06,021
Hold on!

791
01:54:07,901 --> 01:54:09,141
Surrender!

792
01:54:10,941 --> 01:54:13,781
If you see interests,
think then justice.

793
01:54:14,741 --> 01:54:17,821
If you see dangers,
give then your life.

794
01:54:27,381 --> 01:54:28,181
Dongwoo!

795
01:54:53,101 --> 01:54:54,461
Dongwoo!

796
01:54:56,861 --> 01:54:57,701
Sister...

797
01:55:26,461 --> 01:55:28,141
It's the Phantom! Upstairs!

798
01:56:06,661 --> 01:56:08,381
Get people out first.

799
01:56:27,061 --> 01:56:28,141
Stand back.

800
01:56:38,381 --> 01:56:41,581
We're the Shadow Corps, you bastards!

801
01:56:57,101 --> 01:56:58,181
Follow me.

802
01:57:57,221 --> 01:57:57,981
Catch him!

803
01:57:58,021 --> 01:57:58,941
Hold tight!

804
02:00:37,301 --> 02:00:38,461
Don't you get tired?

805
02:00:41,941 --> 02:00:46,421
Why are you so relentless?
What is Joseon?

806
02:00:47,941 --> 02:00:48,941
Murayama!

807
02:00:51,821 --> 02:00:53,101
Drop your weapon!

808
02:00:55,981 --> 02:00:57,101
Sir!

809
02:02:46,741 --> 02:02:52,221
Go on... Continue fighting,
generation after generation,

810
02:02:54,261 --> 02:02:56,061
forever.

811
02:03:04,301 --> 02:03:09,901
You're going to lose anyway.

812
02:04:18,541 --> 02:04:23,581
Don't feel sorry for surviving.

813
02:04:26,941 --> 02:04:28,621
It's not that...

814
02:04:29,901 --> 02:04:34,901
It's so cramped

815
02:04:35,741 --> 02:04:37,421
and so dark...

816
02:04:40,941 --> 02:04:44,021
I feel sorry to put him here.

817
02:04:49,301 --> 02:04:52,261
We'll go above ground one day.

818
02:04:52,621 --> 02:04:53,781
All of us.

819
02:05:35,981 --> 02:05:38,181
When we get our country back,

820
02:05:44,541 --> 02:05:46,141
maybe I'll quit smoking.

821
02:05:53,541 --> 02:05:55,501
Why? It'll taste even better.

822
02:06:08,741 --> 02:06:14,061
The new Governor-General's inauguration
was successfully conducted.

823
02:06:14,421 --> 02:06:17,341
More than 300 distinguished guests

824
02:06:17,501 --> 02:06:22,421
have shared the joy and vision of
Joseon under the leadership

825
02:06:22,461 --> 02:06:25,981
of the newly appointed
Governor-General.

826
02:06:26,901 --> 02:06:32,661
In the wake of the recent
terrorist disturbance,

827
02:06:33,261 --> 02:06:37,501
we find there are still some people

828
02:06:37,541 --> 02:06:40,301
undeserving of advanced civilization
and all its benefits.

829
02:06:41,221 --> 02:06:45,261
And so, as of today's inauguration,

830
02:06:45,341 --> 02:06:47,941
I resolve to establish one empire!

831
02:06:50,421 --> 02:06:52,741
Move your car.
You're causing a traffic jam.

832
02:06:52,781 --> 02:06:55,181
A man is hurt, heartless bastard!

833
02:06:57,061 --> 02:06:58,141
Hey, you bastards!

834
02:07:11,101 --> 02:07:12,181
What is it?

835
02:07:14,301 --> 02:07:15,741
I'll look into it, sir.

836
02:07:18,061 --> 02:07:20,381
Find out what's going on.

837
02:07:20,421 --> 02:07:21,381
Yes, sir.

838
02:07:36,141 --> 02:07:41,781
WANTED

839
02:08:08,381 --> 02:08:09,621
From Phantom

840
02:08:09,661 --> 02:08:10,941
We'll commence the operation

841
02:08:10,981 --> 02:08:12,621
We shall not stop

842
02:08:12,701 --> 02:08:15,101
until we succeed

843
02:09:25,141 --> 02:09:32,581
PHANTOM

844
02:09:35,941 --> 02:09:39,781
Written and directed by
Lee Hae-Young

845
02:09:41,261 --> 02:09:44,061
Inspired by the novel
'THE MESSAGE' by MAI JIA

846
